Two paramedics were robbed of their personal belongings while attending to a call in Lawley near Lenasia. JOHANNESBURG - Joburg Emergency Services say two of their officials have been robbed at gunpoint while attending to a call in Lawley near Lenasia. When the paramedics arrived on the scene earlier today they were robbed of their personal belongings by the suspects, who ran off.Spokesperson Nana Radebe say: When the paramedics arrived at the scene, two men pointed guns at them and forced them to lie on the ground before making off with their personal belongings. WATCH: #EMSAttacks: Paramedic assault victims relive their attack(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)